Meijer, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 4:44 PM ET
Food and Staples Retailing

Company Overview of Meijer, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Meijer, Inc. owns and operates supercenters in Wisconsin, Michigan, Illinois, Indiana, Ohio, and Kentucky. The company’s product categories include grocery, health and beauty, baby care, pet care, electronics, toys, sporting goods, home, home improvement and audio, garden and patio, clothing, gift cards, card and party needs, and custom cakes. It also provides bakery and deli, optical, pharmacy, and photo services. In addition, the company operates gas stations. Further, it sells its products through an online store. The company was founded in 1934 and is based in Grand Rapids, Michigan. Meijer, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Meijer Companies, Ltd.


2929 Walker Avenue NWGrand Rapids, MI 49544-9424United StatesFounded in 1934



Phone: 616-453-6711

Fax: 616-791-2572

www.meijer.com







